---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "layout-text"
description: "Typographic content container with vertical rhythm. Provides intelligent spacing between paragraphs, headings, lists, and other block elements."
elementName: layout-text
category: custom
currentPath: /docs/elements/custom-elements/layout-text/
permalink: /docs/elements/custom-elements/layout-text/
---

{% set basicUsageCode %}<layout-text>
  <h2>Article Title</h2>
  <p>First paragraph of content...</p>
  <p>Second paragraph continues...</p>

  <h3>Section Heading</h3>
  <p>Content for this section...</p>

  <ul>
    <li>List item</li>
    <li>Another item</li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    <p>A notable quote...</p>
  </blockquote>
</layout-text>{% endset %}

{% set blogPostCode %}<layout-center data-layout-max="narrow">
  <article>
    <layout-text>
      <h1>Getting Started with Web Components</h1>
      <p class="lead">Learn how to build reusable HTML elements.</p>
      <p>Web Components are built on web standards...</p>
      <h2>Why Web Components?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Work everywhere HTML works</li>
        <li>Don't require a build step</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </article>
</layout-center>{% endset %}

{% set withCenterCode %}<layout-center data-layout-max="narrow">
  <layout-text>
    <h2>Centered Article</h2>
    <p>Combining layout-text with layout-center creates an optimal reading experience.</p>
    <p>This pattern is common for blog posts, documentation, and long-form content.</p>
  </layout-text>
</layout-center>{% endset %}

<browser-window
    src="/docs/examples/demos/layout-text-basic.html"
    url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/text"
    title="Text Layout Demo"
    shadow>
  </browser-window>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Default</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td colspan="4"><em>layout-text has no configurable attributes. It applies consistent typographic spacing automatically.</em></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>The layout-text element creates a container optimized for long-form reading content. It:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sets a maximum line width of 65ch (characters) for optimal readability</li>
      <li>Applies consistent vertical spacing between block elements</li>
      <li>Uses larger margins before major headings (proximity principle)</li>
      <li>Tightens spacing after headings so they associate with their content</li>
      <li>Provides extra breathing room around figures and code blocks</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Live Example</h2>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/layout-text-live.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/layout-text/live"
      title="Typography with vertical rhythm"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic layout-text usage">{{ basicUsageCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Spacing Rules</h2>
    <p>The prose element applies different spacing based on element types:</p>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Context</th>
          <th>Spacing</th>
          <th>Rationale</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Default (between elements)</td>
          <td><code>var(--size-m)</code></td>
          <td>Standard paragraph spacing</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Before h2</td>
          <td><code>var(--size-2xl)</code></td>
          <td>Major section break</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Before h3</td>
          <td><code>var(--size-xl)</code></td>
          <td>Subsection break</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Before h4/h5/h6</td>
          <td><code>var(--size-l)</code></td>
          <td>Minor section break</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>After any heading</td>
          <td><code>var(--size-s)</code></td>
          <td>Associates heading with content</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Between consecutive lists</td>
          <td><code>var(--size-s)</code></td>
          <td>Groups related lists</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Before/after figures and pre</td>
          <td><code>var(--size-l)</code></td>
          <td>Extra breathing room for media</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

